## 4. File by File — What Each New File Does

### CLI commands (`cli/commands/`)

**`add_cmd.py`** — The most complex CLI command. Two modes: interactive (default) and quick (`--quick`). Interactive mode shows Rich tables for domain selection, type selection, and priority guide before each prompt. Validates with Pydantic, writes to Atlas, exports JSON to disk, and suggests the git commit command.

**`export_cmd.py`** — Reads all tests from Atlas and writes them to `test-definitions/` as JSON. Compares existing files on disk with Atlas content and shows a diff preview before overwriting. `--force` skips confirmation. `--domain` filters by domain.

**`edit_cmd.py`** — Loads a test from Atlas, pre-fills all current values in the prompts (Enter keeps current, `-` clears), shows a diff of changes, and asks for confirmation before saving. Re-validates with Pydantic after edits.

**`delete_cmd.py`** — Soft delete: sets status to `deprecated` in Atlas and updates the JSON file. Never physically deletes — everything stays for traceability.

### Code quality

**`pyproject.toml` `[tool.ruff]` section** — Configures ruff with line-length 100, PEP 8 rules (E, W), pyflakes (F), import sorting (I), pyupgrade (UP), bugbear (B), and simplify (SIM). Exception for B008 (FastAPI's `Depends()` pattern).

### Git hooks (`hooks/`)

**`pre-commit`** — Validates staged files: merge markers (blocks), sensitive files like `.env` (blocks), files >500KB (blocks), `__pycache__` (blocks), `breakpoint()`/`pdb` (warns), bare `print()` outside CLI/scripts (warns). On the `main` branch only: runs `ruff check` (blocks on PEP 8 errors) and `ruff format --check` (warns on formatting issues).

**`commit-msg`** — Enforces Conventional Commits: `type(scope): Description`. Validates format, description length (25-170 chars), uppercase first letter, no trailing period, no forbidden words (WIP, TODO, FIXME, etc.). Same rules as the transcendence repository for cross-repo consistency.

**`pre-push`** — Validates commit messages of new commits being pushed. Warns on non-compliant messages and asks for confirmation.

**`log_hook.sh`** — Shared logging utilities (colours, icons, persistent log file at `.git/hook-logs/hook.log`).

**`install.sh`** — Sets `core.hooksPath` to `vendor/hooks/` and verifies permissions.

### Documentation (`docs/`)

**`python-guide.md`** — 12-section Python onboarding guide teaching the language through real code from this repo. Covers project infrastructure files, fundamentals, imports, type hints, Pydantic, async/await, FastAPI, pymongo, patterns, and gotchas from C/JS.

**`usage-guide.md`** — Quick reference for daily operations: setup, commands, domain/priority/type tables, test lifecycle, commit format, troubleshooting, and all Make commands at a glance.

**`how-to-add-a-test.md`** — Updated for v3: three ways to add tests (API, CLI, JSON), three test types (http, bash, manual), Pydantic validation, complete examples for each type.

**`test-template.json`** — Updated with three type blocks (http, bash, manual) as separate sections with comments.

### Fixes

**`core/git_export.py`** — Now filters `None` values at both the top level and inside nested dicts (like `expected`). This prevents `"jwtClaims": null` from appearing in exported JSON files.

**`core/schema.py`** — Enums changed from `(str, Enum)` to `StrEnum` (Python 3.11+ modern syntax, fixes MRO conflict).

