### Next — Dashboard views

Build the three main views in order: test list (table + filters + Run button), live execution (WebSocket streaming), and test form (create/edit with dynamic fields per type). Each view uses libcss components and talks to the FastAPI endpoints.

### Then — CI and team onboarding

Add the QA step to `transcendence` and `mini-baas-infra` CI pipelines: `python -m runner.ci --priority P0`. Run the team onboarding session: 45-minute demo where each developer creates 2 tests using `make add`.

### Criteria for "team-ready" (already met)

A new team member can now:

1. Clone the repo and run `make` → environment set up in under 2 minutes
2. Run `make list` → see all 14 tests from Atlas
3. Run `make add` → create a test with guided prompts, no documentation needed
4. Run `make test` → execute tests and see results
5. Commit with enforced Conventional Commits format
6. Read `docs/usage-guide.md` for quick reference
7. Read `docs/python-guide.md` to understand the codebase

